|pecorelle~ sembra confermare tale ipotesi". R. Hollander (^comm. ad
loc~.) fa notare come la massima del v. 78 sia stata interpretata non
^in bono~ forse per la prima volta dalla Frankel: "Virgil's ^captatio
benevolentiae~ here, like the one he addressed to Cato in the first
canto (^Purg~ I.70-84), reveals, as M. Frankel has been perhaps
alone in arguing (in G.C. Alessio - R. Hollander [a cura di], ^Studi
americani su Dante~, Milano, Angeli, pp.  122-24), another example of
his not understanding his own limitations.  His epigrammatic concluding
